  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>A form of parallelism that splits the actual weights of the model across devices.</html:p>
    <html:ul><html:li>Large weight matrices split across devices. Can train larger models that exceed memory of single device.</html:li>
  <html:li>Devices exchange partial activations to compute layer outputs.</html:li></html:ul>
